'''Fubarite''' is an informal name and [[in-joke]] in [[geology]] for any [[rock (geology)|rock]] that has been severely [[breccia]]ted and [[metamorphism|metamorphosed]] to the point that it is difficult or impossible to determine its origin.<ref>[http://forums.randi.org/showthread.php?p=2505532 Sandstone - Page 6 - JREF Forum<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://dml.cmnh.org/1999Oct/msg00319.html Schist<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://coding.derkeiler.com/Archive/Delphi/borland.public.delphi.non-technical/2005-05/msg06378.html Re: Delphi 7 Pro. Purchase<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The name is a [[word play]] with the acronym [[List of military slang terms#FUBAR|FUBAR]], which means "fucked up beyond all recognition".<ref>{{cite book|title=A Field Guide to Gold, Gemstone and Mineral Sites of British Columbia |date=1999 |publisher=Orca Book Publishers |page=7 |first1=Richard Dennis |last1=Hudson |first2=Richard |last2=Hudson |first3=Rick |last3=Hudson |quote=The change can be small (slate is simply shale that has been cooked for a few millennia), or it can be so dramatic you can't tell what the original material was (sometimes known as fubarite = “fudged up beyond all recognition”)!}}</ref>
