{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}} {{see also|Sea Odyssey: Giant Spectacular}} [[File:Giants2014_OM1.jpg|thumb|Grandmother, Little Girl and Xolo at Newsham Park, 25 July 2014]] '''Memories of August 1914''' was a five-day outdoor [[performance art]] event featuring giant [[marionette]]s, and took place in [[Liverpool]], England, from 23 to 27 July 2014.<ref name=BBC>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-25629598 |title=Sea Odyssey giants return to Liverpool for WW1 commemoration |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=7 January 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2014}}</ref> The event started with the sleeping Grandmother on display in [[St George's Hall, Liverpool|St George's Hall]].<ref name=Grandmother>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-28459596 |title=Liverpool Giants: 20,000 visit 'sleeping' Grandmother |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=24 July 2014 |accessdate=24 July 2014}}</ref> On the Friday, approximately 300,000 people watched the giants in the city.<ref name=Friday>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-28499361 |title=Liverpool Giants: Thousands watch second day of marionette show |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=26 July 2014 |accessdate=26 July 2014}}</ref> On the final day, the giants left the city in a boat on the [[River Mersey]], after making their way from [[Clarence Dock (Liverpool)|Clarence Dock]] via The Strand.<ref name=river>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-28509698 |title=Liverpool Giants: Marionettes sail away in river boat finale |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=27 July 2014 |accessdate=27 July 2014}}</ref> Crowd estimates show that over the course of the weekend, more than 1.5 million people attended the event. <ref name=crowd>{{cite web |url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/whats-on/arts-culture-news/liverpool-giants-return-city-reveals-7523127 |title=The Giants may be on the way back to Liverpool, reveals city Mayor Joe Anderson |publisher=[[Liverpool Echo]] |date=28 July 2014 |accessdate=29 July 2014}}</ref>
It was designed and operated by the French street theatre company [[Royal de Luxe]],<ref name=Standout>{{cite web |url=http://standoutmagazine.co.uk/giant-puppets-return-liverpool-commemorative-ww1-event/ |title=Giant puppets return to Liverpool for commemorative WW1 event |publisher=Standout Magazine |date=7 January 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2014}}</ref> and featured two of the three giants, the Little Giant Girl and her dog, Xolo, that were used in the [[Sea Odyssey: Giant Spectacular]] in 2012.<ref name=BBC></ref><ref name=LivConf>{{cite web |url=http://www.liverpoolconfidential.co.uk/Culture/Arts/Confirmed-There-will-be-giants |title=Confirmed: There will be giants |publisher=Liverpool Confidential |date=7 January 2014 |accessdate=7 January 2014}}</ref> The event is to mark 100 years since the start of [[World War I]].<ref name=BBC></ref>
==See also== * ''[[La Princesse]]'', a 15-metre (50-foot) mechanical spider that roamed around Liverpool in 2008 * [[The Sultan's Elephant]], an event performed by Royal de Luxe in London in 2006, and in other cities
