'''Pet shipping''' is an industry that involves transporting [[pet]]s, often by plane. This service is commonly used when the animal's owner is moving house (in which case, in the United States, it is [[Tax deduction|tax deductible]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080917215827/https://www.irs.gov/newsroom/article/0,,id=173193,00.html|title=Moving Expenses Related to a New Job May Be Tax Deductible|date=17 September 2008|website=Web.archive.org|accessdate=11 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/p521.pdf|format=PDF|title=Moving Expenses : For use in preparing 2017 Returns|website=Irs.gov|accessdate=11 July 2018}}</ref> However, it can also be used when transporting animals for other reasons, to [[Conformation show|dog shows]], for instance. The worldwide Industry body for Pet Shipping is IPATA (ipata.org)

